<html xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office"
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40">

<head>
<meta http-equiv=Content-Type content="text/x-ms-odc; charset=utf-8">
<meta name=ProgId content=ODC.Table>
<meta name=SourceType content=OLEDB>
<meta name=Catalog content=PRIMSBM>
<meta name=Table content="dbo.sp_qlik_prims_sap_diff">
<title>PRIMS vs SAP-PRODHANA Diff (Qlik live feed)</title>
<xml id=docprops><o:DocumentProperties
  xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office"
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40">
  <o:Name>PRIMS vs SAP-PRODHANA Diff (Qlik live feed)</o:Name>
  <o:Description>SCRUM-31: live link to dbo.sp_qlik_prims_sap_diff on the PRIMSBM SQL Server. Feeds the Excel sheet that the Qlik app reads.</o:Description>
 </o:DocumentProperties>
</xml>
<xml id=msodc><odc:OfficeDataConnection
  xmlns:odc="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:odc"
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40">
  <odc:Connection odc:Type="OLEDB">
   <odc:ConnectionString>Provider=SQLOLEDB.1;Integrated Security=SSPI;Persist Security Info=False;Initial Catalog=PRIMSBM;Data Source=192.168.100.5;Use Procedure for Prepare=1;Auto Translate=True;Packet Size=4096</odc:ConnectionString>
   <odc:CommandType>SQL</odc:CommandType>
   <odc:CommandText>EXEC dbo.sp_qlik_prims_sap_diff @OnlyDifferences = 1</odc:CommandText>
  </odc:Connection>
 </odc:OfficeDataConnection>
</xml>
</head>

<body>
<!--
  ADJUST BEFORE USE:
    * Data Source        -> the PRIMSBM SQL Server hostname/IP (default 192.168.100.5).
    * Integrated Security -> uses the Windows account running Excel. To use a
      dedicated read-only SQL login instead, replace "Integrated Security=SSPI"
      with "User ID=<login>;Password=<pwd>" (prefer a SELECT/EXECUTE-only login,
      never sa).

  IMPORTING INTO EXCEL (establishes the LIVE link — not a static export):
    Data > Get Data > From File > From ODC / or double-click this .odc, then
    "Enable" the connection. The sheet is now bound to the stored procedure.

  REFRESH CADENCE (SCRUM-31 = every 30 min + manual): after importing, set
    Data > Queries & Connections > (this connection) > Properties:
      [x] Refresh every  30  minutes
      [x] Refresh data when opening the file
    Manual refresh at any time: Data > Refresh All (Ctrl+Alt+F5).
  Note: Excel's timed refresh only runs while the workbook is OPEN. For an
  unattended 30-minute refresh on a server, use qlik/refresh_qlik_diff.ps1
  driven by the Windows Task Scheduler task in qlik/Refresh-QlikDiff-Every30Min.xml.
-->
</body>
</html>
